blog.name: julesfalkhunter
blog.title: fragments of broken dreams . . .
blog.description:
All the photographs posted here are original work from photographers I follow  on tumblr . My aim is  twofold, share the inspiration, and give photographers a bit more exposure .     
 I am also part of the  Lux Lit  team of rebloggers, and ms-excuse me with Thierry Facon, where the main focus is to bring you lesser known photographs that we feel deserve some more attention. 
 Please feel free to contact me if you have any questions or comments, or would  like me to check out your blog;  I'm on a constant quest for new photography blogs to follow .
julesfalkhunter@gmail.com

blog.name: brambles-hearts-blog
blog.title: Bramble's Heart's Blog
blog.description:
This is a random blog about randomness shit.
Art/Ask/RP/18+ blog/Multifandom
Post are mostly drawn and/or written.
There will be gore, dark themes, and cursing. But mostly just funny shit.
I draw video games, IRL stuff, random fandoms and NSFW, sometimes. Lots of stuff really.
Response is usually fast unless I'm doing something. Might have to wait for an hour or so. But if it's something big, like going to the hospital or a tragedy, I usually post about it after the event has passed or when it's less stressful.
Roleplay is private (NSFW and/or SFW). I RP mostly one liners to paragraphs. Genre is an open bag for me.
Also sorry for the bad art. I'm just using what I have and to the best of my ability.
Anonymous are allowed!
(Description may change randomly. Scatter brained a bit.)
Enjoy!

summary: The man who fell in love with the moon The first painting of 2019 is finished. It's inspired by the wonderful musical concept...
caption:
The man who fell in love with the moon

The first painting of 2019 is finished. It’s inspired by the wonderful musical concept album “Luna”. It’s a story about a Prince named Alvar (left) who falls in love with the moon god Ishtar (right).

You can listen to the music here: https://open.spotify.com/album/6AoQh2iAZbkBUKsatLiA1v

I hope you like it. Prints are available via Society6 (there’s a sale today with 30% off)

✦ Like my work? Leave me a tip at Ko-Fi. Thanks so much ♥
